// TEST: Unit Array Division Velocity
// The full unitful-array flow: distances / time-scalar broadcast gives
// velocity-signature elements (meters/seconds), compatible with a
// declared velocity unit; reduce keeps element units; an array function
// argument with MATCHING element units is accepted.
Unit meters
Unit seconds
Unit velocity = meters / seconds
type SIdx = Idx<3>
let dists: Array<Float<meters> like SIdx> = [10.0, 20.0, 30.0]
let dt: Float<seconds> = 2.0
let vels = dists / dt
let vcap: Float<velocity> = 100.0
let fastest = vels((2 : SIdx))
let margin = vcap - fastest
function total_v(v: Array<Float<velocity> like SIdx>) -> Float<velocity> = reduce(v, (+))
let vsum = total_v(vels)
// EXPECT: vels = [5.0, 10.0, 15.0]
// EXPECT: margin = 85
// EXPECT: vsum = 30
